tip.text: A very good traditionally made Taiwanese style pork chop rice. The sour pickles r on the sweeter end but tastes great with the set. Only down side was the one side dish that wasn't authentic.

tip.text: Salty clam, radish egg, sweet potato porridge, 3 cup chicken and cod dish, ask very Taiwanese and delish!

venue.name: 欣葉 Shin Yeh Taiwanese Cuisine

tip.text: Bottled Ice lemon tea.. instead get regular soft drinks with infinite refill ftw. The King has their croquet in it, quite good. Will be back to try more.
good latte, on the light side. Pour over is nice.
$130+pp for 3 course fine dining awesome view is not bad. It wasn't "wow" impressive but all dishes were nicely done and very delicious. Love the corn crab entree. Famous choc cake was OK for me..
Awesome latte, love the tint of sweetness in the blend <3
1st timer, had Jumbo pork loin chawamushi set $30. Free flow rice & cabbage only. Surprisingly very good tonkotsu!  Menu overall too expensive imo, but it's a good alternative to ma maison now :)

tip.text: Had the shabu buffet.. Fantastic wagyu and salmon fillets! Great service from the Indian manager too. Definitly come again :)
Beef bibimba is good. Love the way the veggies are spread all over!
Hainan chicken rice is average, but a very cleaned taste. Sauce has some lemon juice makes it refreshing.
Hainan chicken rice above average. Not bad. Love the hotness in the Sauce!

tip.text: Had the normal charashi Don with chawamushi and weekday special spicy sashimi sides. Overall quite good, would come back again.  Nice staffs, keep up the good service.
Great place,  good coffee!
The blood sausage is strong, not for the tainted heart! Try their croissants with extra egg fillings :)
Great coffee, ham cheese croissant is nicely done too!!

tip.text: First time had a fried beef noodle and was very disappointed at its size. Not worth the value at all.

tip.text: New place good beans Great Latte. Too bad they only open around 10am when the center opens.
Yep the BBQ bun is the must, Radish cake and rice noodle roll is pretty good too. Chicken feet here is too average. They no take away but u can: line up>seat>order>ask for take away container ($)..
Came here early dinner with a 10ppl group, didn't have much expectation after online reviews but it turned out good for us. All my friends loved it. Semi-full inc drinks $40pp.

The staff always thinks we order too much... And their kitchen always give less meat than we ordered. So make sure u complaint about it if it happens. Then they started to treat u better. Friday good.
One of the best chicken rice, nuff said.
My Viet friend took me here when I told them I want to eat best 'combination broken rice' nearby.Though their rice isn't authentically all small broken rice but it is indeed one of the best I've had.

tip.text: 2nd time here, another tick for their Kakuni (special marinate pork) tonkotsu ramen. Nice $3.80 takana rice too.  But a big no-no for their katsu curry at the price of $17.80..
Came on 30/12 and still a 15ppl que but didn't wait long till I tried their famous Chicken roll - so good!  Pork roll was devine too :) one of the best in Sydney defibitely
Awesome breakfast and free honey tasting! Very cosy Sunday morning time!
2nd time here.  Hainan chicken as good though this time they stuffed up the rice using non Jasmin rice.. And it really made an impact to my non picky taste bud.
Had the Guilas Eggs with smoked salmon today, not bad but I'll stick with the corn fritter next time for +$2. Coffees always good! :)
Still the best since my first time 1994! The lamb the curry beans the chickens and that chilli! U know its good when we still come here even after uni days!
Had sweet & spicy KFC and it was best I've had here in Sydney (better than naruone), $30 for 2-3ppl not bad. The standard Jajangmyun is so-so as it's bit blend, I'll try seafood version next time.
a Korean franchise? Nice hippy joint, though waiters are acting too casual.. Latte are not bad but on the much more milkier side. Will come try again to follow up.
Lunch special $600 is pretty good and worth it!

Stuffed chicken wing best! Red duck curry surprisingly gooood too~
Very nice art & very excellent coffee today!
